  <description><![CDATA[<p>The MAD Mount Hotel is the perfect place to come back to at the end of the day, just steps away from the Nendaz telecabine, right in the centre of the resort. With a modern design, sustainability at the forefront and a relaxing spa, you’re in for a treat.</p>
<h2>Seven wellness amenities</h2>
<p>After a long day exploring the beautiful mountains on foot, you can reset your body in the spa area. With plenty of tailored features, you can indulge in the Japanese Onsen hot spring, or stimulate blood circulation and soothe your feet in the unique Kneipp hydrotherapy basin. Open from midday, these services are available until the evening, making the ultimate experience whenever you need it.</p>
<h2>Protecting the environment</h2>
<p>This hotel is MAD about protecting the planet, making it their priority to help reduce carbon footprint whilst still providing high quality services at the same time. All the way down to the finer details of organic natural toiletries, you will make a positive contribution too without realising. Solar panels on the roof generate more electricity than consumed, and sustainably sourced Swiss wood results in a gorgeous natural finish. Plus, for every three nights of your stay, MAD Mount Hotel pledges to plant a tree in a deforested part of a European country.</p>
<h2>Comfortable cabins and delicious food</h2>
<p>Fall back onto the cosy bed, surrounded by a modern alpine design and simple but practical decorative finishing touches. With quirky cabins and warm lighting, you are set for a perfect night's sleep. Wake up feeling fresh as you refuel at the hot and cold buffet breakfast for another busy day of adventure or relaxation, the choice is yours. Featuring their own restaurant and terrace, the MAD Mount Hotel is great for trying appetising international dishes with glorious panoramic mountain views.</p>]]></description>
